Stratasys F270 3D Printer

The Stratasys F270 3D Printer, a member of the F123 Series, offers a build volume of 305 x 254 x 305 mm (12 x 10 x 12 in.) and offers a wide range of materials.

Stratasys F123 Series is the world’s most reliable range of industrial-grade 3D printers. Designed for the way you work, they are built on 30 years of research and development by a team of engineers, designers, educators and manufacturers. That means 100% accuracy, engineering grade outputs and repeatable results. Every time.

The F123 Series works with a range of materials – so you can produce complex parts with flexibility and accuracy. And it includes advanced features like Fast Draft mode for truly rapid prototyping, and soluble support to prevent design compromise and hands-on removal. All designed to shorten your product development cycle and keep you ahead of the competition.

The four F123 series printers – F120, F170, F270 and F370 – support a range of capabilities and budgets. F123 provides a solution for every stage of your work cycle, from prototypes to manufacturing floor solutions.

All our F123 series printers deliver:

  • Minimal setup – simply plug and print. Give your entire workgroup access to professional industrial grade 3D printing.
  • Non-stop printing – spend less time troubleshooting and more time getting results.
  • Fast and easy material swaps –maximize your team’s productivity.
  • Reliable results – high levels of accuracy and repeatability, with engineering grade materials.
  • Streamlined workflow – Go directly from CAD file formats to 3D print with GrabCAD Print software.

Stratasys F270

Maximum Build Size (XYZ):
305 x 254 x 305 mm / (12 x 10 x 12 in.)

Model Materials:
PLA, ABS, ASA, FDM TPU 92A, QSR Support material

    Get an inside look at the F123™ Series
    See the difference for yourself

    What makes the F123 Series the most reliable 3D printers? Go behind the scenes and get an up-close look at the materials, quality components, research and more that guarantees the Stratasys F123 printers are accurate, reliable, safe and easy to use.

    Discover the difference between the Stratasys F123 Series and typical desktop printers.

    Explore

    Specifications

    System Size and Weight

    • Stratasys F120: 889 x 870 x 721 mm (35 x 35 x 29 in.), 124kg (275 lbs)
    • Stratasys F170, F270, F370: 1626 x 864 x 711 mm (64 x 34 x 28 in.) 227 kg (500 lbs) with consumables

    Build Size

    • Stratasys F120 & F170: 254 x 254 x 254 mm (10 x 10 x 10 in.)
    • Stratasys F270: 305 x 254 x 305 mm (12 x 10 x 12 in.)
    • Stratasys F370: 355 x 254 x 355 mm (14 x 10 x 14 in.)

    Layer Thickness

    • 0.330 mm (0.013 in.)
      ABS, ASA, PC-ABS
    • 0.254 mm (0.010 in.)
      FDM TPU 92A, PLA, ABS, ASA, PC-ABS
    • 0.178 mm (0.007 in.)
      ABS, ASA, PC-ABS
    • 0.127 mm (0.005 in.)
      ABS, ASA, PC-ABS

    Accuracy

    • Parts are produced with an accuracy of +/- .200 mm (.008 in), or +/- .002 mm/mm (.002 in/in), whichever is greater.

    Software

    Enjoy a smooth 3D printing workflow powered by the intuitive GrabCAD Print software. GrabCAD Print simplifies the preparation, scheduling, monitoring and reporting of all print jobs. And the software also helps to ensure an efficient workflow to streamline job management in shared offices and model shops.

    • Print directly from CAD
    • Stay up to date with notifications
    • Monitor material levels
    • Organize print queues
    • Optimize part features with Advanced FDM controls
